<div id="review_617846012" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/617846012" />
    <a title="Jennifer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7437778-jennifer"><img alt="Jennifer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1624880615p2/7437778.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/617846012?book_show_action=true">May 17, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jennifer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jennifer" href="/user/show/7437778-jennifer">Jennifer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer617846012" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11110436932651055785">I feel this had the potential to be so much more than what it was. While it was a good read and it had a lot of interesting information in it that I was happy to find out about her, this book had a big flaw that was visible throughout the entire book and because of that it got extremely frustrating. While I understand that the author is/was Coretta&apos;s sister, if the biography is about Coretta, it should be about her and not the author with Coretta seeming as something of an afterthought. While sh</span>
  <span id="freeText11110436932651055785" style="display:none">I feel this had the potential to be so much more than what it was. While it was a good read and it had a lot of interesting information in it that I was happy to find out about her, this book had a big flaw that was visible throughout the entire book and because of that it got extremely frustrating. While I understand that the author is/was Coretta's sister, if the biography is about Coretta, it should be about her and not the author with Coretta seeming as something of an afterthought. While she was more present than that of an afterthought, it was extremely hard reading this without continually thinking "I thought this was about Coretta's life and not how you two intertwined." I think that what she did was awesome and loving for her sister and a great way for her to remember her, however I don't think this should have been The Life and Legacy of Coretta Scott King when in reality it was The Life of the Scott Sisters. I think that title would have helped me prepare a lot more for the continuous intertwining of their lives and experiences. I did learn a lot about Coretta which was my goal, so in some ways I'd say that was accomplished. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11110436932651055785" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


